// Test: Zustand store selectors in components
// Each component does multiple useItineraryStore\(\(s\) => s.xxx\) calls.
// For example, ActionBar has 6 separate selectors.
// Each selector creates a separate subscription. When the store updates,
// EACH selector fires, potentially causing multiple re-renders.
// Zustand v5 uses Object.is\(\) for comparison, so primitive selectors are fine.
// But: waypoints and legs are arrays - they create new references on every set\(\).
// So a component subscribing to s.waypoints will re-render on ANY store change
// that calls set\({waypoints: [...]}\).

